```python
import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    module_counts = data['source'].append(data['target']).value_counts()
    sns.histplot(module_counts, bins=20, kde=True)
    plt.xlabel('Number of Dependencies')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of module dependencies?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

```python
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    module_counts = data['source'].value_counts().reset_index()
    module_counts.columns = ['module_id', 'dependency_count']
    
    chart = sns.barplot(x='module_id', y='dependency_count', data=module_counts)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title('Which module has the highest number of dependencies?', wrap=True)
    
    max_dependency_module = module_counts.loc[module_counts['dependency_count'].idxmax()]
    plt.axhline(max_dependency_module['dependency_count'], color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Max: {max_dependency_module['dependency_count']:.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

```python
import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['source_count'] = data.groupby('source')['source'].transform('count')
    data['target_count'] = data.groupby('target')['target'].transform('count')
    data['module_size'] = data['source_count'] + data['target_count']
    
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='module_size', y='source_count')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title('What is the correlation between the number of dependencies and the module size?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

```python
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    dependency_counts = data.groupby(['source', 'target']).size().reset_index(name='count')
    dependency_counts['dependency_type'] = dependency_counts['source'].astype(str) + '->' + dependency_counts['target'].astype(str)
    dependency_counts = dependency_counts.groupby('dependency_type')['count'].sum().sort_values(ascending=False)
    dependency_counts.plot.pie(autopct='%.2f%%')
    plt.title('What is the most common type of dependency between modules?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

```python
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    # Count the number of dependencies per module
    dependencies_count = data.groupby('source').size().reset_index(name='count')
    
    # Create a box plot of the number of dependencies per module
    ax = sns.boxplot(x='count', data=dependencies_count)
    
    # Calculate the average number of dependencies per module
    avg_dependencies = dependencies_count['count'].mean()
    
    # Add a vertical line for the average number of dependencies
    ax.axvline(avg_dependencies, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Average: {avg_dependencies:.2f}')
    
    # Add a legend
    ax.legend()
    
    # Set the title
    plt.title('What is the average number of dependencies per module?', wrap=True)
    
    # Rotate the x axis labels if necessary
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```
